article.headline: ETSU 78, Tennessee Tech 65
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- Kevin Tiggs scored 23 points and Courtney Pigram had 22 points to lead East Tennessee State to a 78-65 victory over Tennessee Tech on Monday night. Mike Smith added 11 points and 10 rebounds, his sixth career double-double, for the Buccaneers (3-2). ETSU took a 16-point lead in the opening seconds of the second half, but Tennessee Tech (3-1) went on a 10-1 run to cut the lead to 47-44 with 11:15 remaining in the game. Tiggs, however, scored 10 points to lead a surge that built ETSU's lead to 67-54 with 3:34 remaining. The Buccaneers outrebounded Tennessee Tech 42-31. Daniel Northern scored 20 points, Will Barnes had 13 and D.J. Lindsay added 10 points for Tennessee Tech.
